Standard Bank has announced the appointment of Zweli Manyathi to succeed outgoing group personal and business bank (PBB) CEO Peter Schlebusch Schlebusch is said to be taking a four-month sabbatical from the company, beginning in April, but he will be returning to the company in a position yet to be announced. “Peter put an enormous amount of time, effort and energy into building the great business that PBB has become,” Group CEO Sim Tshabalala said in a statement on Friday. “Peter has been equally dedicated and successful in leading the group’s modernisation as it becomes a digital financial services organisation. I am immensely grateful to Peter for his unwavering commitment to the Standard Bank Group.” READ MORE: Standard Bank appoints Lungisa Fuzile as CEO Manyathi previously held the role of PBB CEO for Africa regions responsible for growing the bank’s personal and business banking units in African regions outside of the country. He holds a BCom Honours in Financial Management and he’s completed both the Wits Business School and Harvard Business School’s senior executive programmes. “During his tenure in this role, Zweli greatly strengthened our PBB client franchise and grew client revenues substantially,” Tshabalala said. 